      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "even if <code>compareTo</code> is not required to return 1, 0, or -1; it is <i>generally</i> not recommended to use subtraction to compare <code>int</code> due to the risk of overflow or underflow (certainly not a problem with dates, but can be a problem in other use cases) - IMO using <code>Integer.compare()</code> is also better for readability (I want to compare, not subtract)"
    } ],
