    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Java 8 alleviates some of the boilerplate for sorting by particular fields with <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/Comparator.html#comparing-java.util.function.Function-\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>Comparator.comparing</code></a>.</p>\n<pre><code>dateList.sort(Comparator.comparing(Date::getYear)\n                  .thenComparing(Date::getMonth)\n                  .thenComparing(Date::getDay));\n</code></pre>\n<p>Better still, if you use <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/time/LocalDate.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>LocalDate</code></a> instead then your date objects will already be comparable, and you won't need a comparator at all.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 322981,
      "reputation" : 346727,
      "user_id" : 642706,
