    "answer_id" : 79777717,
    "question_id" : 42903042,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<h2><code>java.time.LocalDate</code></h2>\n<p>No need to store year, month, and day as separate fields. Simply use <code>java.time.LocalDate</code> class, built into Java 8+.</p>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/25/docs/api/java.base/java/time/LocalDate.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>java.time.LocalDate</code></a> class knows how to sort its objects, having implemented <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/25/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/Comparable.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>Comparable</code></a>. So no need to compare each field of year-month-day.</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>record Employee( String name , LocalDate hired ) { }\n\nSequencedCollection &lt; Employee &gt; employees =\n        new ArrayList &lt;&gt;(\n                List.of(\n                        new Employee( &quot;Alice&quot; , LocalDate.of( 2021 , Month.JANUARY , 23 ) ) ,\n                        new Employee( &quot;Bob&quot; , LocalDate.of( 2025 , Month.FEBRUARY , 23 ) ) ,\n                        new Employee( &quot;Carol&quot; , LocalDate.of( 2018 , Month.MARCH , 23 ) ) ,\n                        new Employee( &quot;Davis&quot; , LocalDate.of( 2021 , Month.DECEMBER , 23 ) )\n                )\n        );\n\nSequencedCollection &lt; Employee &gt; seniority =\n        employees\n                .stream()\n                .sorted(\n                        Comparator\n                                .comparing( Employee :: hired )\n                                .thenComparing( Employee :: name )\n                )\n                .toList();\n\nseniority.forEach( System.out :: println );\n</code></pre>\n<p>When run:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-none prettyprint-override\"><code>Employee[name=Carol, hired=2018-03-23]\nEmployee[name=Alice, hired=2021-01-23]\nEmployee[name=Davis, hired=2021-12-23]\nEmployee[name=Bob, hired=2025-02-23]\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
