  "title" : "Use compareTo for year, month and day",
  "body" : "<p>I want to sort the dates out on the screen, but when I use <code>compareTo</code> method, I can only use it with one of the Date attributes: year, month or day, not all of them. This is a custom class, not <code>java.util.Date</code> class.</p>\n<p>I am required to sort it out on the screen using <code>compareTo</code> method.</p>\n<p>This is what I have done.</p>\n<pre><code>public int compareTo(Date date) {\n    if(getYear()-date.getYear()&gt;0 &amp;&amp; getMonth()-date.getMonth()&gt;0){\n        \n        return 1;\n    }\n    if(getYear()-date.getYear()&lt;0 &amp;&amp; getMonth()-date.getMonth()&lt;0 ){\n        \n        return -1;\n    }\n    return 0;\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
}